<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-26T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-26T16:00:00-05:00" n="289" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1172.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-26T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1914, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your April 21, 10 p.m. Owing to representations made to the Department
                            that vessel was necessary at Puerto Plata for protection of American and
                            other interests on account of bombardment of city, <hi rend="italic">Wheeling</hi> has been ordered to proceed to that port. In case of
                            absolute necessity <hi rend="italic">Petrel</hi> may be ordered to Santo
                            Domingo. She is now at Port au Prince.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>